Comment (src/views/control-implementations/IndexView.vue:70):
**Medium — inner catalog-loading `<Message>` is unreachable.**

`loading` is computed as `profileBindingsLoading || catalogLoading || controlImplementationLoading` (line 257–262). When `catalogLoading` is true, the outer `v-if="loading"` fires and the entire `v-else` block is hidden — so this inner `v-if="catalogLoading"` can never render. This was pre-existing, but the PR converted it from a plain `<div>` so it's worth fixing here.

**Fix option A** — Remove `catalogLoading` from the `loading` computed so the outer spinner only covers the profile/requirement fetch phase. The inner catalog message then renders correctly for the catalog phase.

**Fix option B** — Drop the inner catalog message and rely on the outer spinner for all loading phases, updating its text to something like "Loading..." that covers all three stages.
