Comment (src/views/control-implementations/partials/ControlStatementImplementation.vue:784):
**Medium (e2e confirmed) — `components.value.push()` in `handleComponentCreated` doesn't trigger reactivity.**

`handleComponentCreated` (line 954) does `components.value.push(newComponent)` to add the new component to the local list. But `useDataApi` stores its `data` as a `shallowRef` — which only tracks reference reassignment, not in-place array mutations. So `componentItems` never recomputes, and the newly created component doesn't appear in the dropdown without a full page reload.

**Fix in `handleComponentCreated`:**
```ts
// replace:
if (components.value) {
  components.value.push(newComponent);
}
// with:
components.value = [...(components.value ?? []), newComponent];
```
Assigning a new array reference is tracked by `shallowRef` and will cause `componentItems` to recompute correctly.
