Comment (src/views/control-implementations/partials/IndexControlImplementation.vue:165):
**Medium (e2e confirmed) — dark mode hover colour uses `@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark)` but the app uses class-based dark mode.**

Tailwind is configured with `darkMode: 'class'` (the `.dark` class on the root). The `<style>` block at lines 260–270 uses `@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark)` for the hover highlight, which only fires when the *OS* is in dark mode. When a user manually enables the app's dark theme without the OS matching, the hover falls back to the light-mode colour `rgb(243 244 246)` (gray-100) — a very bright white on the new `dark:bg-slate-900` background, which was made darker by this PR.

**Fix:** Replace the media-query rule with a class selector, e.g.:
```css
/* remove: */
@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
  .part-display .hover { background-color: rgb(71 85 105); }
}

/* add: */
:global(.dark) .part-display .hover {
  background-color: rgb(71 85 105);
}
```
Or use a Tailwind `dark:` utility class on the part element directly and drop the `<style>` block.
