Comment (src/views/control-implementations/partials/ControlStatementMetadata.vue:85):
**Low — `label` prop is ignored because the default slot overrides it.**

```html
<Button label="Edit Statement">Edit</Button>
```
In Volt/PrimeVue, when both the `label` prop and a default slot are provided, the slot content wins. The rendered button says "Edit"; `label="Edit Statement"` is silently discarded.

Pick one: remove the `label` prop and keep the slot, or remove the slot and use `label="Edit Statement"` only.
