Comment (src/views/control-implementations/partials/ControlStatementSuggestions.vue:88):
**Low — `formatRelevanceScore` called twice per suggestion per render.**

```html
<span v-if="formatRelevanceScore(suggestion.relevanceScore)">
  Relevance: {{ formatRelevanceScore(suggestion.relevanceScore) }}
</span>
```
Two identical calls for the same argument. Extract to a local variable in the render or use a template `v-memo`:
```html
<template v-for="suggestion in displayedSuggestions" :key="suggestion.componentUuid">
  <!-- ... -->
  <template v-if="formatRelevanceScore(suggestion.relevanceScore) as score">
    <span class="text-xs text-gray-500">Relevance: {{ score }}</span>
  </template>
</template>
```
Or just inline the check: `v-if="typeof suggestion.relevanceScore === 'number' && !isNaN(suggestion.relevanceScore)"`.
