Comment (src/views/control-implementations/partials/__tests__/ControlStatementSuggestions.spec.ts:97):
**Low — button-index assumption is brittle.**

`buttons[0]` is assumed to be "Apply All Suggestions" and `buttons[1]` the first suggestion chip. If the DOM order of buttons in the template ever changes, these assertions will silently test the wrong behaviour.

Prefer finding by accessible text or role:
```ts
const applyAllButton = wrapper.findAll('button').find(b => b.text().includes('Apply All Suggestions'));
const firstSuggestionButton = wrapper.findAll('button').find(b => b.text().includes('Component One'));
await applyAllButton?.trigger('click');
await firstSuggestionButton?.trigger('click');
```
